{
  "name": "getCampaignBatch",
  "description": "Returns a single Batch instance for a given batch id. This API is useful for determining the state of a validating batch",
  "parameters": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "id": {
        "format": "int64",
        "type": "integer",
        "description": "An id of a batch"
      },
      "fields": {
        "type": "string",
        "description": "Limit fields received in response. E.g. fields: id, name or fields items (id, name), see more at [partial response](https://developers.callfire.com/docs.html#partial-response) page."
      }
    },
    "required": [
      "id"
    ]
  },
  "handler": "http",
  "request": {
    "method": "GET",
    "url": {
      "$uri": "https://api.callfire.com/v2/campaigns/batches/{id}{?fields}"
    }
  },
  "responses": {
    "200": {
      "$encode": "markdown",
      "$block": [
        {
          "$h1": "Object"
        },
        "A batch represents a group of contacts which can be dialed or texted via call/text broadcast",
        "**Key properties:**",
        {
          "$ul": [
            "**broadcastId**: An id of broadcast which batch belongs to",
            "**created**: A date and time when batch was created, formatted in unix time milliseconds. Example: 1473781817000 for Sat, 05 Jan 1985 14:03:37 GMT",
            "**enabled**: An enabled batch. If batch is disabled its contacts remain undialed/untexted",
            "**id**: A id of a batch",
            "**name**: A batch name",
            "**remaining**: A number of contacts remaining undialed/untexted",
            "**size**: A total number of contacts in batch",
            "**status**: A status of batch (NEW, VALIDATING, ERRORS, SOURCE_ERROR, ACTIVE). NEW - batch is queued for validation; VALIDATING - batch is currently validating; ERRORS - batch is processed, some validation errors occurred; SOURCE_ERROR - if contact source is contact list in CallFire system and it has an error; ACTIVE - batch is processed and ready"
          ]
        },
        {
          "$lang": "json",
          "$code": {
            "$encode": "json",
            "$indent": true,
            "$content": {
              "$": "$.body"
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
